{
  "doc_id": "2692",
  "text": "The special functions associated with linear ODEs frequently happen to be particular cases of some generalized hypergeometric p F q functions [CITATION_1] . One natural approach is thus to directly search for p F q solutions instead of special function solutions of one or another kind, and this is the approach discussed here. Related computer algebra routines were implemented in 2007 and are now at the root of the Maple (release 12) ability for solving non-trivial 3rd order linear ODE problems.",
